    "id": "363",
    "title": "Opioid Risk Tool (ORT) for Narcotic Abuse",
    "desc": "The Opioid Risk Tool for Narcotic abuse estimates risk of opioid-related aberrant behaviors based on patient history.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16336480",
                "text": "Webster LR, Webster RM. Predicting aberrant behaviors in opioid-treated patients: preliminary validation of the Opioid Risk Tool. Pain Med. 2005 Nov-Dec;6(6):432-42. PubMed PMID: 16336480."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "",
                "text": ""
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Addition of the selected points. Complete scoring information can be found in the <a href=\"https://painmedicine.oxfordjournals.org/content/6/6/432#T2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">derivation study</a>.</p>",
        "facts": "<p>Score interpretation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Low risk: 0&ndash;3.</li>\n<li>Moderate risk: 4&ndash;7.</li>\n<li>High risk: &ge;â€Š8.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Other Notes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>185 patients were followed in chronic pain clinic.</li>\n<li>Tracked to determine who developed \"aberrant behaviors\".</li>\n<li>Developed a score based on this to calculate this risk.</li>\n<li>Of note, still 5% of \"low-risk\" patients still had aberrant behaviors..</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Aberrant behaviors included a long list of behaviors indicating possible abuse, including but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Used additional opioids than those prescribed.</li>\n<li>Requested refills instead of clinic visit.</li>\n<li>Canceled clinic visit.</li>\n<li>Solicited opioids from other providers.</li>\n<li>Unauthorized ER visits.\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Pain"
        ],
        "disease_treated": [
            "Chronic Pain"
        ],
        "logic": "var calc_output = [];\nvar u = 0;\nif (age_16_45 == 1) { u += 1 }\nif (depression == 1) { u += 1 }\nif (psychological_disorder == 1) { u += 2 }\nif (alcohol_abuse == 1) { u += 3 }\nif (illegal_drug_abuse == 1) { u += 4 }\nif (prescription_drug_abuse == 1) { u += 5 }\nif (family_prescription_drug == 1) { u += 4 }\nif (sex == 0) {\n    if (family_illegal_drug == 1) { u += 3 }\n    if (family_alcohol == 1) { u += 3 } } else if (sex == 1) {\n    if (sexual_abuse == 1) { u += 3 }\n    if (family_illegal_drug == 1) { u += 2 }\n    if (family_alcohol == 1) { u += 1 } }\nvar msg = '';\nvar mini_msg = '';\nif (u < 4) { msg = 'Low risk for future opioid-related aberrant behaviors. 5.6% of low-risk patients had aberrant behaviors.';\n    mini_msg = 'Low risk' }\nif (u > 3 && u < 8) { msg = 'Moderate risk for future opioid-related aberrant behaviors. 28% of moderate-risk patients had aberrant behaviors.';\n    mini_msg = 'Moderate risk' }\nif (u > 7) { msg = 'High risk for future opioid-related aberrant behaviors. 91% of high-risk patients had aberrant behaviors.';\n    mini_msg = 'High risk' }\ncalc_output.push({ \n    name: 'mini', \n    value: u.toFixed(0), \n    value_text: 'points', \n    message: mini_msg \n});\ncalc_output.push({ \n    name: '1757_Opioid Risk Tool_result', \n    value: u.toFixed(0), \n    value_text: 'points',\n    message: msg \n});",
